  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Configures a session according to command line arguments, runs a search, and prints the result to standard output.
      Parameters:
      args - the command line arguments passed to the program

    • configure

      public static void configure(Session session, CommandLineArguments arguments, boolean verbose) throws Exception
      Configures the given session according to the command line arguments.
      Parameters:
      session - the session object whose settings will be configured
      arguments - the command line arguments describing how to configure the session
      verbose - if true, details of the problem and search will be printed to standard output while the session is configured
      Throws:
      Exception - if any required command line arguments are missing or formatted incorrectly, or if the session throws an exception while it is being configured (for example, if the parser fails to parse the problem)
